WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.465 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.465 --> 00:00:16.830 align:middle line:90%


00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:18.820 align:middle line:10%
Do you ever find
yourself locked

00:00:18.820 --> 00:00:21.760 align:middle line:10%
in to totally nonproductive
styles of conversation

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:23.140 align:middle line:10%
with the people closest to you?

00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:25.330 align:middle line:10%
Perhaps you have
a pattern of blame

00:00:25.330 --> 00:00:27.320 align:middle line:10%
or passive aggressive
behavior and can't

00:00:27.320 --> 00:00:28.790 align:middle line:10%
seem to find your way out.

00:00:28.790 --> 00:00:30.690 align:middle line:10%
If this is the case,
you may find today's

00:00:30.690 --> 00:00:33.060 align:middle line:10%
conversation extremely useful.

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:34.990 align:middle line:84%
John Kinyon has
been a facilitator

00:00:34.990 --> 00:00:37.060 align:middle line:84%
in the modality
called nonviolent

00:00:37.060 --> 00:00:39.540 align:middle line:90%
communication for 15 years.

00:00:39.540 --> 00:00:42.370 align:middle line:84%
From couples to tribes
in Afghanistan and even

00:00:42.370 --> 00:00:44.920 align:middle line:84%
his own children, John
has mastered the skill

00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:46.850 align:middle line:84%
of taking the other
person's concerns

00:00:46.850 --> 00:00:50.850 align:middle line:84%
and needs into consideration
first before taking them on.

00:00:50.850 --> 00:00:53.120 align:middle line:84%
John is going to be doing
a couple of live sessions

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:54.750 align:middle line:84%
in the studio today
to show us how

00:00:54.750 --> 00:00:56.960 align:middle line:90%
it works, beginning with me.

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:01.361 align:middle line:84%
I'm a particularly bad traveler
in the eyes of the TSA people.

00:01:01.361 --> 00:01:02.060 align:middle line:90%
Mmm.

00:01:02.060 --> 00:01:05.170 align:middle line:84%
And that is because I become
confrontational with them.

00:01:05.170 --> 00:01:06.300 align:middle line:90%
Mmhmm.

00:01:06.300 --> 00:01:08.110 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure you haven't--
this is not the first

00:01:08.110 --> 00:01:09.430 align:middle line:84%
time you've heard that.
-Right.

00:01:09.430 --> 00:01:11.610 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
-And everybody has their story.

00:01:11.610 --> 00:01:13.020 align:middle line:90%
Yada, yada, yada.

00:01:13.020 --> 00:01:15.530 align:middle line:90%
And it can become very complex.

00:01:15.530 --> 00:01:18.240 align:middle line:84%
And so in a little
bit, you can maybe help

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:20.810 align:middle line:90%
me work through my TSA issues.

00:01:20.810 --> 00:01:22.830 align:middle line:90%
And-- but we have to want to.

00:01:22.830 --> 00:01:24.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is really the
first tenant, isn't it?

00:01:24.770 --> 00:01:25.200 align:middle line:84%
Yes.
Yes.

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:28.560 align:middle line:84%
That we have to want
to change our behavior.

00:01:28.560 --> 00:01:29.276 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:01:29.276 --> 00:01:30.849 align:middle line:84%
Right.
Yeah.

00:01:30.849 --> 00:01:34.190 align:middle line:84%
So it does take-- it does take
wanting to make that shift.

00:01:34.190 --> 00:01:36.140 align:middle line:10%
Because it's not easy.

00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:39.310 align:middle line:10%
But there is really-- what
I love about this approach

00:01:39.310 --> 00:01:41.670 align:middle line:10%
and what I've learned
is there really is a way

00:01:41.670 --> 00:01:44.500 align:middle line:10%
to change your inner state.

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:48.130 align:middle line:10%
If you're angry, upset,
reactive, stressed.

00:01:48.130 --> 00:01:51.130 align:middle line:10%
There actually is a way
to shift that inside.

00:01:51.130 --> 00:01:54.560 align:middle line:10%
So that literally-- that
whole response and pattern

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:56.900 align:middle line:10%
that goes off in
us can-- can change

00:01:56.900 --> 00:01:58.195 align:middle line:10%
to something more productive.
REGINA: Yeah.

00:01:58.195 --> 00:01:59.380 align:middle line:84%
Once you make the
choice to do it.

00:01:59.380 --> 00:02:00.330 align:middle line:90%
Once you make the choice.

00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:02.500 align:middle line:84%
Because something-- when
you're all ratcheted up,

00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:06.980 align:middle line:84%
there's something in us that's
like-- it's-- we're feeding

00:02:06.980 --> 00:02:08.439 align:middle line:90%
some kind of chemical process--

00:02:08.439 --> 00:02:09.370 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:02:09.370 --> 00:02:11.150 align:middle line:84%
 --that is-- has its
own self-gratification.

00:02:11.150 --> 00:02:12.780 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:02:12.780 --> 00:02:14.250 align:middle line:84%
On some level.
JOHN: Yeah.

00:02:14.250 --> 00:02:16.021 align:middle line:84%
And we have to
choose to come down.

00:02:16.021 --> 00:02:16.720 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yep.

00:02:16.720 --> 00:02:19.660 align:middle line:84%
And disengage from that
cascade of chemicals

00:02:19.660 --> 00:02:21.340 align:middle line:84%
that we must be getting
something out of

00:02:21.340 --> 00:02:23.830 align:middle line:84%
or we wouldn't do these things.
-Yeah.

00:02:23.830 --> 00:02:24.610 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:24.610 --> 00:02:25.800 align:middle line:90%
So definitely.

00:02:25.800 --> 00:02:28.320 align:middle line:84%
Once that-- especially
once it gets going,

00:02:28.320 --> 00:02:32.740 align:middle line:84%
it's hard to pull it
back and be able to have

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:34.590 align:middle line:84%
that part of our
mind that wants--

00:02:34.590 --> 00:02:37.060 align:middle line:84%
knows that maybe that--
reacting that way

00:02:37.060 --> 00:02:38.411 align:middle line:84%
isn't going to get
us what we want.

00:02:38.411 --> 00:02:39.110 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:02:39.110 --> 00:02:41.120 align:middle line:84%
But in that moment,
it might feel

00:02:41.120 --> 00:02:45.210 align:middle line:84%
gratifying to be really angry
or righteous or like that.

00:02:45.210 --> 00:02:48.830 align:middle line:84%
But that-- it's sort of
accessing-- practicing

00:02:48.830 --> 00:02:50.430 align:middle line:84%
to access that part
of us the kind of

00:02:50.430 --> 00:02:53.310 align:middle line:84%
knows that that
isn't what's really

00:02:53.310 --> 00:02:54.500 align:middle line:90%
going to create what we want.

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:56.100 align:middle line:84%
Isn't really going to
produce the world we want.

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:56.990 align:middle line:90%
Well, it is interesting.

00:02:56.990 --> 00:02:59.860 align:middle line:84%
But when you get in those
kinds of situations or couples

00:02:59.860 --> 00:03:02.160 align:middle line:84%
who go head to
head in arguments,

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:04.350 align:middle line:84%
we don't even, at
that point, care

00:03:04.350 --> 00:03:06.130 align:middle line:84%
if we're getting what we want.
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:03:06.130 --> 00:03:07.675 align:middle line:84%
We have totally
lost all perspective.

00:03:07.675 --> 00:03:08.450 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:03:08.450 --> 00:03:09.420 align:middle line:90%
For the most part.

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:10.510 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's what happened.

00:03:10.510 --> 00:03:11.443 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Just takes over. yeah.

00:03:11.443 --> 00:03:14.235 align:middle line:84%
Where this thing, these
chemicals, start taking over.

00:03:14.235 --> 00:03:15.110 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:03:15.110 --> 00:03:17.780 align:middle line:84%
And, well-- I
mean, we have time.

00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:19.920 align:middle line:84%
So if you want we
can-- before we

00:03:19.920 --> 00:03:22.370 align:middle line:84%
start getting into all the
explanations of how Marshall

00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:25.360 align:middle line:84%
Rosenberg began nonviolent
communication and all, which

00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:26.060 align:middle line:90%
we will get into.

00:03:26.060 --> 00:03:28.690 align:middle line:84%
We want to give some
background on that so people

00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:29.880 align:middle line:90%
understand the history of it.

00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:31.590 align:middle line:84%
But we can go
ahead, if you want,

00:03:31.590 --> 00:03:34.110 align:middle line:84%
and just kind of get right into
how you would work with someone

00:03:34.110 --> 00:03:35.240 align:middle line:90%
like me who has issues.

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:35.940 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:35.940 --> 00:03:36.640 align:middle line:90%
Sure.

00:03:36.640 --> 00:03:39.840 align:middle line:84%
I go through-- I go
through TSA twice a week

00:03:39.840 --> 00:03:42.386 align:middle line:84%
because I live in one state
and I work in another.

00:03:42.386 --> 00:03:43.140 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:03:43.140 --> 00:03:44.840 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going
through an airport

00:03:44.840 --> 00:03:47.031 align:middle line:84%
that-- and you'll hear the
chip in my voice I'm sure.

00:03:47.031 --> 00:03:47.730 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:03:47.730 --> 00:03:51.643 align:middle line:84%
That I consider to be extremely
punitive in its procedures.

00:03:51.643 --> 00:03:52.510 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Mmhmm.

00:03:52.510 --> 00:03:53.970 align:middle line:90%
If you choose to opt out.

00:03:53.970 --> 00:03:54.970 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Mmhmm.
Mmhmm.

00:03:54.970 --> 00:03:56.247 align:middle line:84%
Which I don't want to go
through those machines.

00:03:56.247 --> 00:03:57.041 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Mmhmm.
Mmhmm.

00:03:57.041 --> 00:03:59.270 align:middle line:84%
I don't--I mean, for
a variety of reasons.

00:03:59.270 --> 00:04:00.875 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to go
through those machines.

00:04:00.875 --> 00:04:01.610 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:04:01.610 --> 00:04:02.310 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:04:02.310 --> 00:04:03.780 align:middle line:90%
And so that's where it starts.

00:04:03.780 --> 00:04:07.500 align:middle line:84%
It's a-- I very politely
say, oh, opt out.

00:04:07.500 --> 00:04:08.501 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yep.
And then it starts.

00:04:08.501 --> 00:04:09.200 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:04:09.200 --> 00:04:11.230 align:middle line:84%
Now you start your
engagement with personnel.

00:04:11.230 --> 00:04:14.510 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise you're just a
digit that moves through.

00:04:14.510 --> 00:04:15.950 align:middle line:90%
Your stuff moves through.

00:04:15.950 --> 00:04:18.040 align:middle line:84%
Put your hands up in
the air in the machine.

00:04:18.040 --> 00:04:18.999 align:middle line:90%
And you just go.

00:04:18.999 --> 00:04:19.970 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:04:19.970 --> 00:04:22.380 align:middle line:84%
You usually don't encounter
any further conversation.

00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:25.700 align:middle line:84%
But if you choose to opt out,
there's a lot of conversation.

00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:26.760 align:middle line:90%
So you want to work with that?

00:04:26.760 --> 00:04:29.861 align:middle line:84%
I can show you one
of our processes to--

00:04:29.861 --> 00:04:31.330 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yeah.
- --work with that.

00:04:31.330 --> 00:04:32.230 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yeah.
-Yeah?

00:04:32.230 --> 00:04:33.460 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yeah, I
can work with that.

00:04:33.460 --> 00:04:34.160 align:middle line:90%
Yeah?

00:04:34.160 --> 00:04:35.960 align:middle line:84%
And then maybe
you can help-- help

00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:42.190 align:middle line:84%
me understand maybe the lack
of wisdom in my approach.

00:04:42.190 --> 00:04:44.500 align:middle line:84%
I mean-- because I'm doing
the kind of a dual purpose

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:47.230 align:middle line:84%
thing in here when I start
getting a little mouthy

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:48.800 align:middle line:84%
with them about
trying to re-educate

00:04:48.800 --> 00:04:51.051 align:middle line:84%
them on the realities of 9/11.
Which--

00:04:51.051 --> 00:04:52.090 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHTER]
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:04:52.090 --> 00:04:52.789 align:middle line:90%
Isn't--

00:04:52.789 --> 00:04:54.201 align:middle line:84%
Isn't always warmly
received, maybe.

00:04:54.201 --> 00:04:54.900 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:04:54.900 --> 00:04:56.450 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: It's not
always warmly received.

00:04:56.450 --> 00:04:57.040 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
Yeah.

00:04:57.040 --> 00:04:59.112 align:middle line:90%
They're not thanking you for--

00:04:59.112 --> 00:05:00.544 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: You know what?
-Yeah?

00:05:00.544 --> 00:05:02.040 align:middle line:84%
Two people recently
have thanked me.

00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:02.390 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Ah.

00:05:02.390 --> 00:05:03.656 align:middle line:84%
Two of the people
that have patted me

00:05:03.656 --> 00:05:06.061 align:middle line:84%
down actually asked what
the name of the book

00:05:06.061 --> 00:05:07.300 align:middle line:84%
was I was referring--
JOHN: Ah.

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:09.730 align:middle line:84%
I was talking to-- about, in
this case, Judy Wood's book.

00:05:09.730 --> 00:05:11.430 align:middle line:84%
I've interviewed
a couple of times

00:05:11.430 --> 00:05:13.350 align:middle line:84%
and I have a lot
of respect for it.

00:05:13.350 --> 00:05:15.640 align:middle line:84%
So of course-- so for me
it's feeling violated.

00:05:15.640 --> 00:05:16.350 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Uh huh.

00:05:16.350 --> 00:05:17.410 align:middle line:90%
I feel violated.

00:05:17.410 --> 00:05:20.010 align:middle line:84%
So I feel like we should--
none of us in this line

00:05:20.010 --> 00:05:21.480 align:middle line:84%
should have to be
going through this.

00:05:21.480 --> 00:05:23.860 align:middle line:90%
So it's a-- carrying a torch.

00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:28.360 align:middle line:84%
Well, let me show you how-- one
of our processes in our Mediate

00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:32.110 align:middle line:84%
Your Life training, this is
one that we-- if I was working

00:05:32.110 --> 00:05:34.650 align:middle line:84%
with you kind of as a
conflict coach or something,

00:05:34.650 --> 00:05:37.110 align:middle line:84%
I could kind of work with
you through through this.

00:05:37.110 --> 00:05:39.200 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm going to do--
there are three parts of it.

00:05:39.200 --> 00:05:43.290 align:middle line:84%
And as I go through those
parts, some distinctions

00:05:43.290 --> 00:05:45.580 align:middle line:84%
and communication language I'm
going to be kind of pointing

00:05:45.580 --> 00:05:47.650 align:middle line:90%
to as I'm working with you.

00:05:47.650 --> 00:05:50.460 align:middle line:84%
One has to do with separating
out what you observed,

00:05:50.460 --> 00:05:51.370 align:middle line:90%
kind of what happens--

00:05:51.370 --> 00:05:52.070 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:05:52.070 --> 00:05:54.595 align:middle line:84%
 --from your thoughts
and beliefs and kind

00:05:54.595 --> 00:05:56.150 align:middle line:84%
of--your interpretations.
REGINA: OK.

00:05:56.150 --> 00:05:56.940 align:middle line:90%
Your story about it.

00:05:56.940 --> 00:05:59.100 align:middle line:90%
Just to keep that separate.

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:00.325 align:middle line:90%
And often that's hard to do.

00:06:00.325 --> 00:06:01.110 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:06:01.110 --> 00:06:02.110 align:middle line:90%
And another is your feelings.

00:06:02.110 --> 00:06:03.470 align:middle line:84%
So I want to talk
about your feelings.

00:06:03.470 --> 00:06:06.800 align:middle line:84%
But a lot of times we mix up
our feelings with our thoughts.

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:11.320 align:middle line:84%
And so I'll be asking you
to kind of separate that out

00:06:11.320 --> 00:06:13.070 align:middle line:84%
and how I reflect back
what I'm hearing you say

00:06:13.070 --> 00:06:14.200 align:middle line:90%
and questions to ask.

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:16.780 align:middle line:84%
And finally, to get to
what your needs are.

00:06:16.780 --> 00:06:21.441 align:middle line:84%
This language for the qualities
we all want as human beings.

00:06:21.441 --> 00:06:22.140 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:06:22.140 --> 00:06:26.051 align:middle line:84%
That we all want respect
or love or consideration.

00:06:26.051 --> 00:06:27.130 align:middle line:84%
Those things.
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:06:27.130 --> 00:06:28.700 align:middle line:84%
But we often mix
that up with-- we

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:30.620 align:middle line:84%
call the strategies,
the specific things

00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:32.210 align:middle line:84%
that we want to meet our needs.
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:06:32.210 --> 00:06:33.330 align:middle line:84%
Often that's all
mixed together.

00:06:33.330 --> 00:06:36.290 align:middle line:84%
So I'll be sort of piecing
that, kind of separating that

00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:37.320 align:middle line:90%
out as well as we're talking.

00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:38.130 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: OK.
-OK?

00:06:38.130 --> 00:06:38.240 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:06:38.240 --> 00:06:39.360 align:middle line:84%
And we won't do an hour
session, obviously.

00:06:39.360 --> 00:06:39.770 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: No.

00:06:39.770 --> 00:06:40.736 align:middle line:90%
We'll just do a little quick.

00:06:40.736 --> 00:06:42.990 align:middle line:84%
Well, just-- get through it
in, you know, five, ten minutes.

00:06:42.990 --> 00:06:43.170 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:06:43.170 --> 00:06:45.290 align:middle line:84%
However long it takes for
me to get something through.

00:06:45.290 --> 00:06:45.989 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:06:45.989 --> 00:06:48.400 align:middle line:84%
So let's start with this--
with the first part.

00:06:48.400 --> 00:06:49.180 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:52.920 align:middle line:84%
Which is what you experience
inside of yourself.

00:06:52.920 --> 00:06:54.760 align:middle line:84%
So you've said you
start to go through.

00:06:54.760 --> 00:06:56.637 align:middle line:84%
You say you want to
go through-- you don't

00:06:56.637 --> 00:06:57.970 align:middle line:84%
want to go through
the machine, you want

00:06:57.970 --> 00:06:59.040 align:middle line:90%
to go through the pat down.

00:06:59.040 --> 00:07:01.380 align:middle line:84%
And you-- then you
said that there

00:07:01.380 --> 00:07:05.440 align:middle line:84%
was a certain way that they
treat you that you don't like.

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:08.040 align:middle line:84%
So some things that
you've perceived.

00:07:08.040 --> 00:07:10.980 align:middle line:84%
So say a few more
words about what-- what

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:13.480 align:middle line:90%
happens that you don't like.

00:07:13.480 --> 00:07:15.600 align:middle line:84%
Well, I first go through
my own self-dialogue.

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:16.730 align:middle line:90%
When I show up, I think.

00:07:16.730 --> 00:07:17.690 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:07:17.690 --> 00:07:19.620 align:middle line:84%
Make this a happy day.
Right?

00:07:19.620 --> 00:07:22.560 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'll talk to myself
about, let's just--let's just

00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:23.390 align:middle line:90%
sail through here.

00:07:23.390 --> 00:07:24.580 align:middle line:84%
It's probably going to be a
nice lady on the other side.

00:07:24.580 --> 00:07:25.970 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Try to keep yourself.
Yeah.

00:07:25.970 --> 00:07:27.830 align:middle line:84%
Keep it positive.
Yeah.

