JOHN: There's a sadness there.

00:20:58.640 --> 00:20:59.340 align:middle line:90%
A sadness.

00:20:59.340 --> 00:21:00.040 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:21:00.040 --> 00:21:02.260 align:middle line:84%
Because the-- and
the being violated,

00:21:02.260 --> 00:21:04.540 align:middle line:84%
the effort is to shift the
thought of being violated

00:21:04.540 --> 00:21:06.830 align:middle line:84%
to seeing these
behaviors you don't like

00:21:06.830 --> 00:21:09.380 align:middle line:84%
and then connecting to
the need for respect,

00:21:09.380 --> 00:21:11.600 align:middle line:90%
autonomy, consideration.

00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:12.880 align:middle line:90%
Kind of basic treatment--

00:21:12.880 --> 00:21:14.750 align:middle line:90%
And give it out first.

00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:16.610 align:middle line:84%
Give it to the
other person first.

00:21:16.610 --> 00:21:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And just set a different
pattern and rapport.

00:21:18.860 --> 00:21:19.989 align:middle line:90%
I'll try that when I got home.

00:21:19.989 --> 00:21:20.855 align:middle line:90%
That's something you can--

00:21:20.855 --> 00:21:22.736 align:middle line:90%
DIA is the most harsh airport.

00:21:22.736 --> 00:21:23.710 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:21:23.710 --> 00:21:24.910 align:middle line:84%
I'll send them a bill too.
Yeah.

00:21:24.910 --> 00:21:26.389 align:middle line:84%
Send them a bill too.
Yeah.

00:21:26.389 --> 00:21:28.120 align:middle line:84%
I'll be flying out
tomorrow, and so I'll

00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:29.170 align:middle line:90%
let you know how that goes.

00:21:29.170 --> 00:21:30.180 align:middle line:90%
But no, I could feel it.

00:21:30.180 --> 00:21:32.700 align:middle line:84%
I was starting to get teared
up and I was starting to feel

00:21:32.700 --> 00:21:33.850 align:middle line:90%
what was really underneath it.

00:21:33.850 --> 00:21:35.930 align:middle line:90%
And so this is wonderful.

00:21:35.930 --> 00:21:36.630 align:middle line:90%
It's an example.

00:21:36.630 --> 00:21:38.400 align:middle line:84%
Because I think a
lot of people feel

00:21:38.400 --> 00:21:40.410 align:middle line:84%
they're losing their
autonomy in a lot of ways.

00:21:40.410 --> 00:21:44.340 align:middle line:84%
The presence of CHP, the
presence of-- just the presence

00:21:44.340 --> 00:21:46.120 align:middle line:84%
of authoritative
figures in our lives

00:21:46.120 --> 00:21:49.430 align:middle line:84%
pressing down on us when we're
already under a lot of stress

00:21:49.430 --> 00:21:52.066 align:middle line:90%
right now as a civilization.

00:21:52.066 --> 00:21:52.770 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Mmhmm.

00:21:52.770 --> 00:21:54.478 align:middle line:84%
I mean, these are
pressure filled times.

00:21:54.478 --> 00:21:55.400 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yeah.
Yeah.

00:21:55.400 --> 00:21:58.790 align:middle line:84%
And you and I were talking
off camera about this.

00:21:58.790 --> 00:22:01.420 align:middle line:84%
When it starts ratcheting up--
and this is in everybody--

00:22:01.420 --> 00:22:02.350 align:middle line:90%
well, not everyone.

00:22:02.350 --> 00:22:04.150 align:middle line:84%
But most people are
feeling the stress.

00:22:04.150 --> 00:22:06.790 align:middle line:84%
They may try to dissipate
it through meditation

00:22:06.790 --> 00:22:08.170 align:middle line:90%
and manage it.

00:22:08.170 --> 00:22:12.650 align:middle line:84%
But we're almost feeling this
boiling frog syndrome going

00:22:12.650 --> 00:22:14.550 align:middle line:90%
on where the pressure is on.

00:22:14.550 --> 00:22:15.390 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Mmhmm.

00:22:15.390 --> 00:22:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And so your overview
first for every one of us

00:22:19.680 --> 00:22:22.760 align:middle line:84%
and what we need to do,
I mean using the example

00:22:22.760 --> 00:22:24.600 align:middle line:90%
we just used as well.

00:22:24.600 --> 00:22:27.540 align:middle line:84%
We have to catch how we're
feeling instantly, right?

00:22:27.540 --> 00:22:28.310 align:middle line:90%
Catch it early.

00:22:28.310 --> 00:22:29.076 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Catch it early.

00:22:29.076 --> 00:22:30.620 align:middle line:90%
And to me it's a practice.

00:22:30.620 --> 00:22:33.550 align:middle line:84%
So if I can-- I try to have
a daily-- in our training

00:22:33.550 --> 00:22:34.840 align:middle line:90%
we all invite people.

00:22:34.840 --> 00:22:39.410 align:middle line:84%
Have a daily practice of
presence and self-connection

00:22:39.410 --> 00:22:41.340 align:middle line:90%
to notice when we get triggered.

00:22:41.340 --> 00:22:42.910 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we don't
notice for a while

00:22:42.910 --> 00:22:44.540 align:middle line:84%
and we get all ratcheted
up and it's really

00:22:44.540 --> 00:22:45.650 align:middle line:90%
hard to do anything about it.

00:22:45.650 --> 00:22:47.207 align:middle line:84%
So to notice it
earlier and earlier.

00:22:47.207 --> 00:22:48.440 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: You can feel
it in your body.

00:22:48.440 --> 00:22:49.180 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:22:49.180 --> 00:22:52.110 align:middle line:84%
It's the practice of paying
attention to your body.

00:22:52.110 --> 00:22:54.770 align:middle line:84%
A lot of times we
kind of live up here.

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:58.330 align:middle line:84%
But to pay more-- to have
a daily practice of being

00:22:58.330 --> 00:23:00.870 align:middle line:84%
focused in the body a
little more, being aware of

00:23:00.870 --> 00:23:02.170 align:middle line:90%
am I noticing?

00:23:02.170 --> 00:23:03.350 align:middle line:90%
Am I getting triggered?

00:23:03.350 --> 00:23:06.800 align:middle line:84%
And then something that I
learned as far back as when

00:23:06.800 --> 00:23:10.560 align:middle line:84%
I was in college and deeply
enamored with Mahatma Gandhi

00:23:10.560 --> 00:23:14.520 align:middle line:84%
and the practice of
nonviolence as a way to respond

00:23:14.520 --> 00:23:18.030 align:middle line:84%
to oppressive forces in the
world and conflict-- basically

00:23:18.030 --> 00:23:18.760 align:middle line:90%
conflict.

00:23:18.760 --> 00:23:20.340 align:middle line:84%
That was your way
into all of this.

00:23:20.340 --> 00:23:21.340 align:middle line:90%
That was my way in.

00:23:21.340 --> 00:23:26.210 align:middle line:84%
That I just was so taken with
what this man had come up with

00:23:26.210 --> 00:23:27.070 align:middle line:90%
and the power.

00:23:27.070 --> 00:23:30.660 align:middle line:84%
I saw amazing power
on this huge level.

00:23:30.660 --> 00:23:33.500 align:middle line:84%
And it literally
toppled in India

00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:36.310 align:middle line:84%
the power of the British
Empire at that time.

00:23:36.310 --> 00:23:38.150 align:middle line:84%
And so what were you
taking away from that?

00:23:38.150 --> 00:23:38.290 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:23:38.290 --> 00:23:39.056 align:middle line:90%
So what I took-- yeah.

00:23:39.056 --> 00:23:41.850 align:middle line:84%
What I took away from
that is-- and it's

00:23:41.850 --> 00:23:44.170 align:middle line:84%
been years of really
unpacking and what-- you know,

00:23:44.170 --> 00:23:45.760 align:middle line:90%
what did I learn from that?

00:23:45.760 --> 00:23:49.910 align:middle line:84%
And what I would say now is that
the incredible power of being

00:23:49.910 --> 00:23:55.920 align:middle line:84%
willing to be present
to and face and confront

00:23:55.920 --> 00:23:59.980 align:middle line:84%
in the sense of just meet
and be with those deepest

00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:03.690 align:middle line:84%
fears and that rage and anger,
whatever boils up in us.

00:24:03.690 --> 00:24:06.250 align:middle line:84%
Because we want you to run
away from that inside or we

00:24:06.250 --> 00:24:09.580 align:middle line:84%
want to lash out and blame
others and take-- but if I can

00:24:09.580 --> 00:24:11.880 align:middle line:84%
just-- if I can-- and I
saw that Gandhi do that.

00:24:11.880 --> 00:24:13.730 align:middle line:84%
That was the principle
of nonviolence.

00:24:13.730 --> 00:24:17.440 align:middle line:84%
That he was willing
to suffer, to die.

00:24:17.440 --> 00:24:18.360 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Totally committed.

00:24:18.360 --> 00:24:19.610 align:middle line:90%
And he inspired everyone else.

00:24:19.610 --> 00:24:21.720 align:middle line:90%
That that was freedom.

00:24:21.720 --> 00:24:22.810 align:middle line:90%
That was power.

00:24:22.810 --> 00:24:25.660 align:middle line:84%
If you could sit with
your own deepest fears

00:24:25.660 --> 00:24:28.500 align:middle line:84%
and stay present
and not-- and then

00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:32.640 align:middle line:84%
you could be present to
whatever fears are trying to be

00:24:32.640 --> 00:24:34.160 align:middle line:90%
stimulated from the outside.

00:24:34.160 --> 00:24:37.470 align:middle line:84%
But if we can be present to that
fight, flight, freeze in us.

00:24:37.470 --> 00:24:40.470 align:middle line:84%
That-- it's such a deep
biological reaction.

00:24:40.470 --> 00:24:41.170 align:middle line:90%
It's so powerful.

00:24:41.170 --> 00:24:43.260 align:middle line:84%
And if we're being honest--and
if we're being honest,

00:24:43.260 --> 00:24:44.720 align:middle line:84%
everybody can feel
the second it starts.

00:24:44.720 --> 00:24:46.121 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: In everybody.
You know it.

00:24:46.121 --> 00:24:47.190 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:24:47.190 --> 00:24:48.670 align:middle line:84%
We might call it
different things.

00:24:48.670 --> 00:24:49.910 align:middle line:90%
But it-- it's-- yeah.

00:24:49.910 --> 00:24:51.460 align:middle line:90%
It's a very powerful experience.

00:24:51.460 --> 00:24:54.550 align:middle line:84%
So the commitment is to
be willing to acknowledge

00:24:54.550 --> 00:24:56.550 align:middle line:90%
it and do something about it.

00:24:56.550 --> 00:24:58.840 align:middle line:84%
Instead of what we talked
about in the very beginning,

00:24:58.840 --> 00:25:02.190 align:middle line:84%
having these chemicals basically
take you on their own journey

00:25:02.190 --> 00:25:04.486 align:middle line:84%
into a very screwball
emotional journey.

00:25:04.486 --> 00:25:05.740 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yes.
Yeah.

00:25:05.740 --> 00:25:06.439 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:25:06.439 --> 00:25:08.757 align:middle line:84%
So being willing
to be with it first.

00:25:08.757 --> 00:25:09.890 align:middle line:84%
To me I've found
more and more how

00:25:09.890 --> 00:25:11.210 align:middle line:90%
important that first step is.

00:25:11.210 --> 00:25:12.340 align:middle line:90%
To notice.

00:25:12.340 --> 00:25:15.480 align:middle line:84%
And be with it in a way
that I'm not just letting--

00:25:15.480 --> 00:25:17.650 align:middle line:90%
I'm not reacting to it.

00:25:17.650 --> 00:25:20.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm not-- I'm not--
I'm just being with it.

00:25:20.120 --> 00:25:21.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm not doing anything else.

00:25:21.130 --> 00:25:22.870 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to blame
for the other anymore.

00:25:22.870 --> 00:25:25.880 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to let go of
all my thoughts and stuff.

00:25:25.880 --> 00:25:27.720 align:middle line:84%
And can just feel
it and be with it?

00:25:27.720 --> 00:25:29.730 align:middle line:90%
And then can I go into empathy?

00:25:29.730 --> 00:25:30.480 align:middle line:90%
If I'm willing?

00:25:30.480 --> 00:25:31.450 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yes.

00:25:31.450 --> 00:25:32.580 align:middle line:90%
And you have to be willing.

00:25:32.580 --> 00:25:33.613 align:middle line:90%
You have to be really willing.

00:25:33.613 --> 00:25:35.470 align:middle line:84%
If you have a real
bone with somebody

00:25:35.470 --> 00:25:36.335 align:middle line:90%
it's harder for people.

00:25:36.335 --> 00:25:38.590 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: It's harder, but that's
why we start with-- notice

00:25:38.590 --> 00:25:39.790 align:middle line:84%
how I started with you.
-Yeah.

00:25:39.790 --> 00:25:41.140 align:middle line:84%
When we did the
situation with you,

00:25:41.140 --> 00:25:42.394 align:middle line:84%
I didn't ask you
to go right away,

00:25:42.394 --> 00:25:43.660 align:middle line:84%
what's going on with
the other person?

00:25:43.660 --> 00:25:44.420 align:middle line:90%
Because, right?

00:25:44.420 --> 00:25:47.150 align:middle line:84%
We need-- usually we
need the empathy first.

00:25:47.150 --> 00:25:50.050 align:middle line:84%
We need to get
underneath our reactions

00:25:50.050 --> 00:25:54.890 align:middle line:84%
and all that to get into, what
are those needs underneath?

00:25:54.890 --> 00:25:57.361 align:middle line:84%
Those-- that tender place of
what we really care about.

00:25:57.361 --> 00:25:58.060 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:25:58.060 --> 00:25:59.180 align:middle line:84%
And when you got
there, you said

00:25:59.180 --> 00:26:03.410 align:middle line:84%
you started to feel moved and
touched and kind of what I saw

00:26:03.410 --> 00:26:05.430 align:middle line:84%
is like you got
tuned into a bigger

00:26:05.430 --> 00:26:07.250 align:middle line:84%
picture of what you care about.
REGINA: Right.

00:26:07.250 --> 00:26:08.510 align:middle line:84%
And you got to
sadness and mourning.

00:26:08.510 --> 00:26:11.040 align:middle line:84%
But I sensed also that
inspiration of, yeah.

00:26:11.040 --> 00:26:12.570 align:middle line:84%
That's what I want
for this world

00:26:12.570 --> 00:26:14.610 align:middle line:90%
and for myself and others.

00:26:14.610 --> 00:26:17.990 align:middle line:84%
So if we give ourselves
that, if we can do that,

00:26:17.990 --> 00:26:22.314 align:middle line:84%
then I think we can
really be willing to be

00:26:22.314 --> 00:26:24.079 align:middle line:84%
present to another's experience.
-Yeah.

00:26:24.079 --> 00:26:26.890 align:middle line:84%
Because that defused the
chemical cascade enough

00:26:26.890 --> 00:26:28.390 align:middle line:84%
that it's like, oh, I
see what's going on.

00:26:28.390 --> 00:26:30.271 align:middle line:84%
I'm really sad about what's
happened around here.

00:26:30.271 --> 00:26:31.160 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yeah.
Right.

00:26:31.160 --> 00:26:33.150 align:middle line:84%
And so, you know,
that's starting

00:26:33.150 --> 00:26:34.185 align:middle line:90%
