Because I know Marshall.
JOHN: Yeah.

00:36:51.760 --> 00:36:54.350 align:middle line:84%
Who was the one that really
created this--the whole system

00:36:54.350 --> 00:36:55.840 align:middle line:84%
of nonviolent communication?
JOHN: Yes.

00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:56.650 align:middle line:90%
The protocols for it?

00:36:56.650 --> 00:36:57.730 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:36:57.730 --> 00:36:58.980 align:middle line:90%
That you've been seeing here.

00:36:58.980 --> 00:36:59.820 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yes.

00:36:59.820 --> 00:37:00.830 align:middle line:90%
Marshall was supposed to go.

00:37:00.830 --> 00:37:01.530 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:37:01.530 --> 00:37:02.570 align:middle line:90%
Marshall was supposed to go.

00:37:02.570 --> 00:37:03.270 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:37:03.270 --> 00:37:07.960 align:middle line:84%
So this was early 2002 right
after the-- 9/11 had happened

00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:11.200 align:middle line:90%
and the bombings in Afghanistan.

00:37:11.200 --> 00:37:15.830 align:middle line:84%
And Marshall Rosenberg,
who is my long time mentor

00:37:15.830 --> 00:37:22.890 align:middle line:84%
for over 15 years now, he had
decided to go into the-- he'd

00:37:22.890 --> 00:37:25.330 align:middle line:84%
been invited by
somebody in Pakistan

00:37:25.330 --> 00:37:28.370 align:middle line:84%
to go and work in the refugee
camps along the border.

00:37:28.370 --> 00:37:30.570 align:middle line:84%
So there's this--
just at that point

00:37:30.570 --> 00:37:33.010 align:middle line:84%
especially, just
tons-- so millions

00:37:33.010 --> 00:37:34.010 align:middle line:90%
of people on the border there.

00:37:34.010 --> 00:37:34.920 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:36.280 align:middle line:90%
Afghani refugees.

00:37:36.280 --> 00:37:37.930 align:middle line:84%
And he was going to
go into the camps.

00:37:37.930 --> 00:37:41.190 align:middle line:84%
And my colleague Ike Lasater
and I. We said, hey, Marshall,

00:37:41.190 --> 00:37:41.900 align:middle line:90%
can we go with you?

00:37:41.900 --> 00:37:45.550 align:middle line:84%
It sounded adventurous,
exciting and all that.

00:37:45.550 --> 00:37:46.510 align:middle line:90%
He said, sure.

00:37:46.510 --> 00:37:47.860 align:middle line:84%
And your intention
was you were going

00:37:47.860 --> 00:37:49.447 align:middle line:84%
to create a nonviolent,
peaceful communication

00:37:49.447 --> 00:37:50.280 align:middle line:90%
between warring factions.

00:37:50.280 --> 00:37:51.110 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yeah, we were
going to do a training.

00:37:51.110 --> 00:37:52.620 align:middle line:84%
Well, we were going
to do training.

00:37:52.620 --> 00:37:53.319 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:37:53.319 --> 00:37:56.620 align:middle line:84%
We were going to offer
these skills and approaches

00:37:56.620 --> 00:37:58.510 align:middle line:84%
to going working on conflict.
REGINA: OK.

00:37:58.510 --> 00:37:59.430 align:middle line:90%
So what happened?

00:37:59.430 --> 00:38:01.530 align:middle line:84%
So Marshall-- it
was too dangerous.

00:38:01.530 --> 00:38:03.310 align:middle line:84%
Marshall decided, this
is way too dangerous.

00:38:03.310 --> 00:38:05.180 align:middle line:84%
The State Department had
been putting out notices.

00:38:05.180 --> 00:38:06.680 align:middle line:90%
Do not go to Pakistan.

00:38:06.680 --> 00:38:08.660 align:middle line:84%
By all means, do not go
to the northwest frontier

00:38:08.660 --> 00:38:10.530 align:middle line:90%
province area of Pakistan.

00:38:10.530 --> 00:38:14.070 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly where we
had-- were intending to go.

00:38:14.070 --> 00:38:15.830 align:middle line:90%
So Marshall said, no way.

00:38:15.830 --> 00:38:19.321 align:middle line:84%
And for some crazy reason
Ike and I decided to go.

00:38:19.321 --> 00:38:20.720 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Hey, your bags
were packed, right?

00:38:20.720 --> 00:38:22.240 align:middle line:90%
He had already gone ahead.

00:38:22.240 --> 00:38:24.600 align:middle line:84%
And I just--you know,
Marshall I'm gonna--

00:38:24.600 --> 00:38:25.570 align:middle line:90%
and he was like, do not.

00:38:25.570 --> 00:38:26.969 align:middle line:84%
Don't go.
Don't go.

00:38:26.969 --> 00:38:28.590 align:middle line:90%
And I-- I don't know.

00:38:28.590 --> 00:38:29.560 align:middle line:90%
I just feel so compelled.

00:38:29.560 --> 00:38:31.290 align:middle line:90%
So I-- we went.

00:38:31.290 --> 00:38:34.650 align:middle line:84%
And we had a quite a
harrowing adventure

00:38:34.650 --> 00:38:36.530 align:middle line:84%
of trying to do this
without him being there

00:38:36.530 --> 00:38:39.410 align:middle line:84%
and making our way from
Karachi in the south

00:38:39.410 --> 00:38:43.070 align:middle line:84%
all the way up to
Islamabad and then up

00:38:43.070 --> 00:38:45.530 align:middle line:84%
into the Northwest
frontier province.

00:38:45.530 --> 00:38:49.421 align:middle line:84%
And we got into the camps and
we were there for three days

00:38:49.421 --> 00:38:50.120 align:middle line:90%
total.

00:38:50.120 --> 00:38:51.860 align:middle line:84%
And we had this naive
idea we'd just kind

00:38:51.860 --> 00:38:52.895 align:middle line:90%
of walk in and do a workshop.

00:38:52.895 --> 00:38:55.390 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHTER]
And--

00:38:55.390 --> 00:38:58.151 align:middle line:84%
Was there something as like a
language barrier, for example?

00:38:58.151 --> 00:38:58.850 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:38:58.850 --> 00:38:59.600 align:middle line:84%
Had you considered some
of those smaller nuances?

00:38:59.600 --> 00:39:02.430 align:middle line:84%
We had translator.
Well, we had a translator.

00:39:02.430 --> 00:39:04.040 align:middle line:84%
But English was not--
-No, that's not the--

00:39:04.040 --> 00:39:06.210 align:middle line:84%
- --his strong suit.
-Yeah.

00:39:06.210 --> 00:39:09.680 align:middle line:84%
And he knew nothing about
nonviolent communication.

00:39:09.680 --> 00:39:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And-- but we gave
him a crash course.

00:39:11.790 --> 00:39:15.880 align:middle line:84%
And we got up into the-- found
a way to get into the camps.

00:39:15.880 --> 00:39:22.290 align:middle line:84%
And it took a couple days of
just listening to their pain.

00:39:22.290 --> 00:39:23.395 align:middle line:90%
They just-- they didn't--

00:39:23.395 --> 00:39:25.010 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: One can only imagine.

00:39:25.010 --> 00:39:28.100 align:middle line:84%
They just-- so much pain
related to the US, the Soviets.

00:39:28.100 --> 00:39:31.000 align:middle line:84%
Just all that has been happening
their country for so long.

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:32.770 align:middle line:84%
So we did a lot of
listening for a while.

00:39:32.770 --> 00:39:35.040 align:middle line:84%
And we could see-- and we
threw all these-- there

00:39:35.040 --> 00:39:36.824 align:middle line:84%
were about maybe eight
different languages

00:39:36.824 --> 00:39:37.590 align:middle line:90%
that were being spoken.

00:39:37.590 --> 00:39:38.730 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:39:38.730 --> 00:39:40.720 align:middle line:84%
And the different elders
that showed up each day

00:39:40.720 --> 00:39:43.450 align:middle line:84%
to meet with us, there were like
maybe 30 to 40 or maybe even

00:39:43.450 --> 00:39:44.570 align:middle line:90%
more each day.

00:39:44.570 --> 00:39:46.660 align:middle line:84%
And when we were
listening to them, even

00:39:46.660 --> 00:39:49.490 align:middle line:84%
through this translation
that was often very complex

00:39:49.490 --> 00:39:52.950 align:middle line:84%
and I don't know how accurate,
that you could see that we'd

00:39:52.950 --> 00:39:53.810 align:middle line:90%
make an empathy guess.

00:39:53.810 --> 00:39:56.010 align:middle line:84%
We'd just say, you're
feeling this way

00:39:56.010 --> 00:39:58.610 align:middle line:84%
because you have these needs
and they're not being met

00:39:58.610 --> 00:40:00.205 align:middle line:84%
and you're in so
much pain about it.

00:40:00.205 --> 00:40:02.820 align:middle line:84%
And they'd sit back at
times, and then their eyes

00:40:02.820 --> 00:40:04.850 align:middle line:90%
would kind of glisten, moisten.

00:40:04.850 --> 00:40:06.290 align:middle line:90%
Like they got really heard.

00:40:06.290 --> 00:40:07.840 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Mmhmm.
-You know?

00:40:07.840 --> 00:40:10.631 align:middle line:84%
And they saw us as
representing the US and West.

00:40:10.631 --> 00:40:11.330 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:40:11.330 --> 00:40:14.540 align:middle line:84%
And then the third day,
they had been very hospitable

00:40:14.540 --> 00:40:17.000 align:middle line:84%
and they asked us
to go to the mosque,

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:18.500 align:middle line:84%
if we'd go to the
mosque with them.

00:40:18.500 --> 00:40:22.980 align:middle line:84%
And immediately half the room--
it's, again, about 40 elders.

00:40:22.980 --> 00:40:24.260 align:middle line:84%
Say, no.
That's not right.

00:40:24.260 --> 00:40:25.000 align:middle line:90%
That's wrong.

00:40:25.000 --> 00:40:26.264 align:middle line:90%
You can't do that.

00:40:26.264 --> 00:40:27.730 align:middle line:84%
And they started to
fight right in the room.

00:40:27.730 --> 00:40:29.884 align:middle line:84%
They just, you know--this
energy level shot up.

00:40:29.884 --> 00:40:31.050 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yelling at
each other and--

00:40:31.050 --> 00:40:32.670 align:middle line:84%
And yelling and just--
zsh zsh zsh, you know?

00:40:32.670 --> 00:40:33.150 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:40:33.150 --> 00:40:34.250 align:middle line:84%
And I calmed and
I turned to Ike

00:40:34.250 --> 00:40:36.090 align:middle line:84%
and I said, Ike, we
finally have our conflict.

00:40:36.090 --> 00:40:38.251 align:middle line:84%
Because we couldn't really get
a good situation to work on.

00:40:38.251 --> 00:40:38.950 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:40:38.950 --> 00:40:41.090 align:middle line:84%
We've got a conflict to show
them how we can do this.

00:40:41.090 --> 00:40:41.790 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yeah.

00:40:41.790 --> 00:40:43.120 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at me
like, are you crazy?

00:40:43.120 --> 00:40:43.819 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:40:43.819 --> 00:40:45.270 align:middle line:84%
This is a religious
conflict here.

00:40:45.270 --> 00:40:47.780 align:middle line:84%
But I was too excited
to get-- notice.

00:40:47.780 --> 00:40:49.710 align:middle line:84%
And we got everybody
calmed down.

00:40:49.710 --> 00:40:52.270 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up
bringing up one person

00:40:52.270 --> 00:40:54.780 align:middle line:84%
from each side of
that conflict and I

00:40:54.780 --> 00:40:59.970 align:middle line:84%
spent the day mediating between
them in our-- with our process.

00:40:59.970 --> 00:41:03.170 align:middle line:84%
And I got that the
needs from one side

00:41:03.170 --> 00:41:05.820 align:middle line:84%
would say-- say the
side-- the person

00:41:05.820 --> 00:41:08.330 align:middle line:84%
representing the side
that wanted us to come.

00:41:08.330 --> 00:41:10.930 align:middle line:84%
You could--you maybe could
imagine the needs that he was

00:41:10.930 --> 00:41:12.360 align:middle line:90%
trying to meet by asking us.

00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:13.380 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:41:13.380 --> 00:41:16.630 align:middle line:84%
Hospitality.
Connection.

00:41:16.630 --> 00:41:19.310 align:middle line:90%


00:41:19.310 --> 00:41:22.491 align:middle line:84%
Being able to have a sense
of inclusion and community.

00:41:22.491 --> 00:41:23.190 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:41:23.190 --> 00:41:26.170 align:middle line:84%
And so, you know, those kind
of needs that he was trying

00:41:26.170 --> 00:41:28.750 align:middle line:84%
to meet and the others that
were supportive of that

00:41:28.750 --> 00:41:30.340 align:middle line:90%
to want us to come.

00:41:30.340 --> 00:41:34.330 align:middle line:84%
And then on the other
side, got to get him

00:41:34.330 --> 00:41:35.860 align:middle line:90%
clear on what he was wanting.

00:41:35.860 --> 00:41:37.250 align:middle line:84%
Not just what he
thought what was

00:41:37.250 --> 00:41:40.010 align:middle line:84%
wrong about the other guy
and the other approach,

00:41:40.010 --> 00:41:41.460 align:middle line:90%
but what he was wanting.

00:41:41.460 --> 00:41:44.870 align:middle line:84%
And that had to do with respect
and safety for the traditions.

00:41:44.870 --> 00:41:46.141 align:middle line:90%
You're hearing the same words.

00:41:46.141 --> 00:41:47.640 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't matter which
one of us speaking this.

00:41:47.640 --> 00:41:48.660 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: It's universal.

00:41:48.660 --> 00:41:50.591 align:middle line:84%
Human respect thing.
And sovereignty.

00:41:50.591 --> 00:41:51.665 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: The respect.
Sovereignty.

00:41:51.665 --> 00:41:52.640 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:41:52.640 --> 00:41:55.400 align:middle line:84%
But there-- it is
also about honoring.

00:41:55.400 --> 00:41:56.590 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Honoring, yes.

00:41:56.590 --> 00:41:58.080 align:middle line:84%
Honoring the
traditions and safety.

00:41:58.080 --> 00:41:58.780 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:41:58.780 --> 00:42:00.340 align:middle line:84%
This having these
outsiders come

00:42:00.340 --> 00:42:01.930 align:middle line:90%
in and be in a sacred space.

00:42:01.930 --> 00:42:05.790 align:middle line:84%
So it's about honoring the
sacred and being and real sense

00:42:05.790 --> 00:42:09.630 align:middle line:84%
of safety and protection
of their space.

00:42:09.630 --> 00:42:10.890 align:middle line:90%
So I got the needs.

00:42:10.890 --> 00:42:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And I asked them to
say back to each other

00:42:13.140 --> 00:42:15.276 align:middle line:84%
what they heard each
other's needs are.

00:42:15.276 --> 00:42:15.990 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:42:15.990 --> 00:42:18.120 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, we
have to imagine this

00:42:18.120 --> 00:42:21.061 align:middle line:84%
isn't like just a little
tiff between a boyfriend

00:42:21.061 --> 00:42:22.459 align:middle line:84%
and girlfriend.
JOHN: No, this is--

00:42:22.459 --> 00:42:24.720 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about such
deeply entrenched differences.

00:42:24.720 --> 00:42:25.510 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:42:25.510 --> 00:42:26.529 align:middle line:90%
And a history of conflict.

00:42:26.529 --> 00:42:27.851 align:middle line:84%
And even fear and hatred.
JOHN: Yeah.

00:42:27.851 --> 00:42:28.550 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:42:28.550 --> 00:42:32.130 align:middle line:84%
Deep, deep conflict in
that part of the world.

00:42:32.130 --> 00:42:32.900 align:middle line:90%
And so, yeah.

00:42:32.900 --> 00:42:36.450 align:middle line:84%
This was-- but I was just going
through the process with them.

00:42:36.450 --> 00:42:38.070 align:middle line:90%
And they did it.

00:42:38.070 --> 00:42:41.310 align:middle line:84%
They ended up acknowledging
what the other person

00:42:41.310 --> 00:42:42.030 align:middle line:90%
said they wanted.

00:42:42.030 --> 00:42:43.420 align:middle line:84%
And then I turned
to the whole group--

00:42:43.420 --> 00:42:44.819 align:middle line:84%
because there was just
I was working with.

00:42:44.819 --> 00:42:46.340 align:middle line:90%
The whole group was watching.

00:42:46.340 --> 00:42:49.240 align:middle line:10%
And I said, does anybody in this
room not have all those needs?

00:42:49.240 --> 00:42:50.710 align:middle line:10%
All of them?
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:42:50.710 --> 00:42:53.160 align:middle line:10%
There's this pin drop silence.

00:42:53.160 --> 00:42:55.920 align:middle line:10%
And then there was just sort of
smiling and nodding and, yeah.

00:42:55.920 --> 00:42:56.780 align:middle line:10%
Like, yeah.

00:42:56.780 --> 00:42:57.610 align:middle line:10%
They got it.

00:42:57.610 --> 00:42:59.500 align:middle line:10%
And then I asked
them, how about we all

00:42:59.500 --> 00:43:02.140 align:middle line:10%
work together and see
if we can find a way

00:43:02.140 --> 00:43:04.801 align:middle line:10%
to get all those needs met?

00:43:04.801 --> 00:43:06.300 align:middle line:84%
And there again there
were sort of just looks

00:43:06.300 --> 00:43:08.110 align:middle line:90%
of surprise on some faces.

00:43:08.110 --> 00:43:10.250 align:middle line:84%
And then I started-- we
started to look at how could--

00:43:10.250 --> 00:43:13.050 align:middle line:84%
what would be some
ideas, some strategies

00:43:13.050 --> 00:43:14.230 align:middle line:90%
to get those needs met?

00:43:14.230 --> 00:43:16.100 align:middle line:84%
It didn't actually take all
that long at that point.

00:43:16.100 --> 00:43:17.611 align:middle line:84%
A lot of it was just
getting connected.

00:43:17.611 --> 00:43:18.310 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Sure.

00:43:18.310 --> 00:43:19.110 align:middle line:84%
Getting understanding
and connection.

00:43:19.110 --> 00:43:20.143 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Well, that makes sense.

00:43:20.143 --> 00:43:22.940 align:middle line:84%
At this-- to get
out of the thinking

00:43:22.940 --> 00:43:25.660 align:middle line:84%
that's about right and wrong
and who's right and who's wrong,

00:43:25.660 --> 00:43:26.840 align:middle line:90%
who's good, who's bad.

00:43:26.840 --> 00:43:27.540 align:middle line:90%
And all that.

00:43:27.540 --> 00:43:28.680 align:middle line:90%
To get to a connection.

00:43:28.680 --> 00:43:32.230 align:middle line:84%
And then once that happened,
the solution came pretty--

00:43:32.230 --> 00:43:33.730 align:middle line:90%
didn't take all that long.

00:43:33.730 --> 00:43:34.830 align:middle line:84%
It went through
a few iterations.

00:43:34.830 --> 00:43:35.800 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yeah.

00:43:35.800 --> 00:43:38.197 align:middle line:84%
And then when we got
there, to the solution

00:43:38.197 --> 00:43:39.330 align:middle line:84%
that they both
agreed to--and then

00:43:39.330 --> 00:43:40.690 align:middle line:90%
I turned to the whole room.

00:43:40.690 --> 00:43:44.110 align:middle line:84%
And I said-- well, first I
said, so this solution, which

00:43:44.110 --> 00:43:46.170 align:middle line:84%
happened to be we sit right
outside the door and somebody

00:43:46.170 --> 00:43:48.270 align:middle line:84%
would sit with us and they could
tell us what's going on but we

00:43:48.270 --> 00:43:50.014 align:middle line:84%
wouldn't actually go in.
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:43:50.014 --> 00:43:51.480 align:middle line:84%
So that went through
a number of exchanges.

00:43:51.480 --> 00:43:53.960 align:middle line:84%
But then-- everybody-- so
does that meet your needs

00:43:53.960 --> 00:43:56.390 align:middle line:84%
for hospitality and connection?
And yes.

00:43:56.390 --> 00:43:58.560 align:middle line:84%
Does this meet your needs
for respect and honoring

00:43:58.560 --> 00:43:59.570 align:middle line:90%
the traditions and safety?

00:43:59.570 --> 00:44:00.620 align:middle line:90%
Yes, it does.

00:44:00.620 --> 00:44:03.400 align:middle line:84%
And I turned the whole room
and I said, so we did it?

00:44:03.400 --> 00:44:04.520 align:middle line:90%
So that's it?

00:44:04.520 --> 00:44:06.210 align:middle line:84%
And again, there
was this pin drop.

00:44:06.210 --> 00:44:07.457 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Aw.
-Really.

00:44:07.457 --> 00:44:08.290 align:middle line:90%
What a wonderful moment.

00:44:08.290 --> 00:44:10.171 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: It was just this-- and
then they started clapping.

00:44:10.171 --> 00:44:11.290 align:middle line:84%
Oh.
Haha.

00:44:11.290 --> 00:44:12.689 align:middle line:84%
And cheering.
Really.

00:44:12.689 --> 00:44:13.980 align:middle line:84%
The whole room
exploded with energy.

00:44:13.980 --> 00:44:15.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh, that is so wonderful.

00:44:15.920 --> 00:44:18.960 align:middle line:90%
Of people smiling and happy.

00:44:18.960 --> 00:44:19.910 align:middle line:90%
And I-- my--

00:44:19.910 --> 00:44:20.743 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: But look at that.

00:44:20.743 --> 00:44:22.244 align:middle line:84%
And every person is
looking for these things.

00:44:22.244 --> 00:44:24.060 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
To work it out in that way.

00:44:24.060 --> 00:44:24.570 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yeah, and
to work it out--

00:44:24.570 --> 00:44:24.960 align:middle line:90%
Through connection.

00:44:24.960 --> 00:44:26.260 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Yeah, instead of
[INAUDIBLE] each other.

00:44:26.260 --> 00:44:26.965 align:middle line:84%
Through understanding
and working together.

00:44:26.965 --> 00:44:27.664 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:44:27.664 --> 00:44:30.760 align:middle line:84%
So they collaborated
to find a solution

00:44:30.760 --> 00:44:32.700 align:middle line:90%
that met everybody's needs.

00:44:32.700 --> 00:44:34.460 align:middle line:84%
And they were all
excited about that.

00:44:34.460 --> 00:44:37.720 align:middle line:84%
And at the very end, the
most senior elder in the camp

00:44:37.720 --> 00:44:38.930 align:middle line:90%
came up to us.

00:44:38.930 --> 00:44:40.990 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh, I like
very much what you did.

00:44:40.990 --> 00:44:43.700 align:middle line:84%
I try to do things like
that, but, you know, that was

00:44:43.700 --> 00:44:45.460 align:middle line:90%
I was really nice what you did.

00:44:45.460 --> 00:44:46.350 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Aw.

00:44:46.350 --> 00:44:48.530 align:middle line:84%
And he said, if we knew
how to do this we wouldn't

00:44:48.530 --> 00:44:51.190 align:middle line:84%
have to fight any more.
-OK.

00:44:51.190 --> 00:44:52.941 align:middle line:84%
So what better
endorsement is there?

00:44:52.941 --> 00:44:53.640 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:44:53.640 --> 00:44:55.240 align:middle line:84%
For having chosen
that line of work.

00:44:55.240 --> 00:44:57.060 align:middle line:84%
That dharma in your
lifetime to have

00:44:57.060 --> 00:44:58.740 align:middle line:84%
brought that to these people.
JOHN: Yeah.

00:44:58.740 --> 00:45:00.430 align:middle line:84%
And who knows what
the trickle down effect

00:45:00.430 --> 00:45:03.491 align:middle line:84%
was among those people
and their families even.

00:45:03.491 --> 00:45:04.190 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:45:04.190 --> 00:45:06.200 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
I'd like to go next.

00:45:06.200 --> 00:45:08.020 align:middle line:84%
You have done some
intense mediation

00:45:08.020 --> 00:45:10.730 align:middle line:84%
with couples who find
themselves so entrenched they

00:45:10.730 --> 00:45:12.800 align:middle line:90%
just can't find their way out.

00:45:12.800 --> 00:45:14.320 align:middle line:84%
And just to take
five minutes or so

00:45:14.320 --> 00:45:16.360 align:middle line:84%
about maybe a couple
of cases where

00:45:16.360 --> 00:45:18.430 align:middle line:84%
there was such polarization.
JOHN: Oh, yeah.

00:45:18.430 --> 00:45:22.230 align:middle line:84%
And you were able to bring
such healing between them.

00:45:22.230 --> 00:45:24.270 align:middle line:84%
Maybe give us a couple
examples so we can see what's

00:45:24.270 --> 00:45:26.750 align:middle line:84%
possible in case anyone
out here listening to this

00:45:26.750 --> 00:45:30.460 align:middle line:84%
thinks you're in an absolutely
impossible situation

00:45:30.460 --> 00:45:33.660 align:middle line:84%
and you have no options
in terms of how to engage

00:45:33.660 --> 00:45:34.480 align:middle line:90%
with the other person.

00:45:34.480 --> 00:45:35.480 align:middle line:84%
Let's hear this.
-Mmhmm.

00:45:35.480 --> 00:45:36.179 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:45:36.179 --> 00:45:38.540 align:middle line:84%
Well, I regularly come
across those situations

00:45:38.540 --> 00:45:40.030 align:middle line:90%
that seem impossible.

00:45:40.030 --> 00:45:41.960 align:middle line:84%
That the conflict
is just too big.

00:45:41.960 --> 00:45:42.840 align:middle line:90%
There's too much hurt.

00:45:42.840 --> 00:45:43.710 align:middle line:90%
There's too much pain.

00:45:43.710 --> 00:45:46.490 align:middle line:84%
And this one that
you referenced,

00:45:46.490 --> 00:45:50.460 align:middle line:84%
this couple that I worked
with, they were divorced.

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:54.690 align:middle line:84%
And they were having
issues around child support

00:45:54.690 --> 00:45:56.420 align:middle line:90%
and visitation and things.

00:45:56.420 --> 00:45:58.060 align:middle line:84%
And they were-- but
they hadn't actually

00:45:58.060 --> 00:45:59.940 align:middle line:84%
spoken to each other
for years because they

00:45:59.940 --> 00:46:02.390 align:middle line:84%
couldn't tolerate even
having any conversation

00:46:02.390 --> 00:46:03.720 align:middle line:90%
with each other at all.

00:46:03.720 --> 00:46:08.410 align:middle line:84%
And so I talked to them
individually beforehand.

00:46:08.410 --> 00:46:10.420 align:middle line:84%
And they just
basically said, well,

00:46:10.420 --> 00:46:12.940 align:middle line:84%
I don't think-- this is--
there's no hope, really.

00:46:12.940 --> 00:46:16.310 align:middle line:84%
Because I have absolutely no
trust of the other person.

00:46:16.310 --> 00:46:18.454 align:middle line:84%
They both said-- pretty much
the exactly the same thing.

00:46:18.454 --> 00:46:19.320 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: The trust us gone.

00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:22.780 align:middle line:84%
I've been completely betrayed
and I'm deeply just hurt

00:46:22.780 --> 00:46:26.860 align:middle line:84%
and I have no trust and
there's just no hope.

00:46:26.860 --> 00:46:29.670 align:middle line:84%
But we don't have
to go to court.

00:46:29.670 --> 00:46:32.690 align:middle line:84%
And it was going to be a
big, terrible legal battle.

00:46:32.690 --> 00:46:35.094 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted to try to-- this
was like a last ditch effort.

00:46:35.094 --> 00:46:36.481 align:middle line:84%
You were the last ditch effort.
Right.

00:46:36.481 --> 00:46:37.180 align:middle line:90%
Last effort, right.

00:46:37.180 --> 00:46:38.930 align:middle line:84%
But they both were
saying, I can't imagine

00:46:38.930 --> 00:46:40.630 align:middle line:90%
how we can work through this.

00:46:40.630 --> 00:46:42.340 align:middle line:90%
Because there's just so much.

00:46:42.340 --> 00:46:43.760 align:middle line:84%
Now they weren't in
the same room, right?

00:46:43.760 --> 00:46:44.040 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:46:44.040 --> 00:46:45.970 align:middle line:84%
Because they couldn't even
bear to be in the same room.

00:46:45.970 --> 00:46:48.760 align:middle line:84%
One was in a European
country and one

00:46:48.760 --> 00:46:50.430 align:middle line:90%
was in the United States.

00:46:50.430 --> 00:46:51.160 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:46:51.160 --> 00:46:52.450 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: And his was Skype--one
of them was Skyped in.

00:46:52.450 --> 00:46:53.490 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
We were all Skyped.

00:46:53.490 --> 00:46:53.950 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: OK.
-Skyping.

00:46:53.950 --> 00:46:55.150 align:middle line:90%
The three of us.

00:46:55.150 --> 00:46:55.930 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:46:55.930 --> 00:46:58.680 align:middle line:84%
And this took place
over many sessions.

00:46:58.680 --> 00:47:01.300 align:middle line:84%
So lots of individual work
with them to prepare them.

00:47:01.300 --> 00:47:02.925 align:middle line:84%
Like what I did
with you, you know?

00:47:02.925 --> 00:47:04.640 align:middle line:84%
That empathy for
themselves and then

00:47:04.640 --> 00:47:06.690 align:middle line:84%
trying to imagine some
empathy for what was

00:47:06.690 --> 00:47:07.940 align:middle line:90%
going on for the other person.

00:47:07.940 --> 00:47:09.550 align:middle line:90%
And so a lot of work preparing.

00:47:09.550 --> 00:47:13.120 align:middle line:84%
And then-- and then a number--
a number of sessions meeting

00:47:13.120 --> 00:47:16.560 align:middle line:90%
with them together.

00:47:16.560 --> 00:47:18.490 align:middle line:84%
And one of the key things
that I helped them do

00:47:18.490 --> 00:47:21.560 align:middle line:84%
is to notice when they
had an enemy image.

00:47:21.560 --> 00:47:23.730 align:middle line:84%
This phrase that
Marshall Rosenberg

00:47:23.730 --> 00:47:24.800 align:middle line:90%
has used over the years.

00:47:24.800 --> 00:47:26.850 align:middle line:90%
And we picked up on it.

00:47:26.850 --> 00:47:28.260 align:middle line:84%
And call it that
process I did with you

00:47:28.260 --> 00:47:29.480 align:middle line:90%
an enemy image process.

00:47:29.480 --> 00:47:32.260 align:middle line:84%
How do we transform
those images where

00:47:32.260 --> 00:47:34.330 align:middle line:84%
we just see an enemy--
even if the people

00:47:34.330 --> 00:47:35.949 align:middle line:84%
closest to us, right?
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:47:35.949 --> 00:47:38.030 align:middle line:84%
We can still see the
other that's against us.

00:47:38.030 --> 00:47:38.730 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:47:38.730 --> 00:47:39.720 align:middle line:90%
Like she was saying.

00:47:39.720 --> 00:47:42.310 align:middle line:84%
And so how do we
literally-- not just

00:47:42.310 --> 00:47:43.660 align:middle line:84%
have the idea that
we should change it,

00:47:43.660 --> 00:47:45.960 align:middle line:90%
but actually it dissolves away.

00:47:45.960 --> 00:47:49.800 align:middle line:84%
So during the mediation,
as well as before,

00:47:49.800 --> 00:47:53.610 align:middle line:84%
I worked on-- with them on how
to help them notice they had

00:47:53.610 --> 00:47:55.930 align:middle line:84%
that image that they
literally weren't, like, kind

00:47:55.930 --> 00:47:57.410 align:middle line:90%
of seeing the other person.

00:47:57.410 --> 00:47:58.400 align:middle line:90%
They just saw this image.

00:47:58.400 --> 00:48:02.810 align:middle line:84%
And help them be aware of that
and catch that and give them

00:48:02.810 --> 00:48:05.550 align:middle line:84%
enough support in the
moment to keep trying

00:48:05.550 --> 00:48:09.290 align:middle line:84%
to get into-- deeper
and deeper into what

00:48:09.290 --> 00:48:10.630 align:middle line:84%
was going on for each
of them that they

00:48:10.630 --> 00:48:11.420 align:middle line:90%
were trying to express.

00:48:11.420 --> 00:48:13.430 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: They must have had
such deep sadness at the core.

00:48:13.430 --> 00:48:14.640 align:middle line:90%
At the core, it was.

00:48:14.640 --> 00:48:16.030 align:middle line:84%
It was just tremendous grief.
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:48:16.030 --> 00:48:16.729 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:48:16.729 --> 00:48:19.520 align:middle line:84%
But it went from this anger
and bitterness and resentment

00:48:19.520 --> 00:48:21.210 align:middle line:90%
to a lot of grief.

00:48:21.210 --> 00:48:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And they actually started
sharing the grief.

00:48:23.190 --> 00:48:25.060 align:middle line:84%
And they shared
things with each other

00:48:25.060 --> 00:48:27.175 align:middle line:84%
that they couldn't
hear before that.

00:48:27.175 --> 00:48:28.720 align:middle line:84%
Like, there was
more to the story.

00:48:28.720 --> 00:48:31.410 align:middle line:84%
The other person didn't quite
know it or couldn't hear it.

00:48:31.410 --> 00:48:34.310 align:middle line:84%
And they started being able to
really, like, make sense of,

00:48:34.310 --> 00:48:36.590 align:middle line:84%
oh, that's why you did it.
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:48:36.590 --> 00:48:37.290 align:middle line:90%
Ah.

00:48:37.290 --> 00:48:38.480 align:middle line:90%
That's why you did it.

00:48:38.480 --> 00:48:40.660 align:middle line:84%
I could never understand
why you did that.

00:48:40.660 --> 00:48:41.425 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yeah.

00:48:41.425 --> 00:48:44.180 align:middle line:84%
That that stuff started
to come out as well.

00:48:44.180 --> 00:48:46.830 align:middle line:84%
The deep grief
for what they went

00:48:46.830 --> 00:48:50.570 align:middle line:84%
through, and also the
sadness of the impact

00:48:50.570 --> 00:48:52.270 align:middle line:90%
on the other person that--

00:48:52.270 --> 00:48:53.950 align:middle line:84%
And imagine what this
was doing to the life.

00:48:53.950 --> 00:48:55.886 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Oh, and the children.
Yeah.

00:48:55.886 --> 00:48:57.080 align:middle line:84%
Or rather children.
JOHN: Yeah.

00:48:57.080 --> 00:49:00.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, so what you were
able to help them do,

00:49:00.330 --> 00:49:02.410 align:middle line:84%
essentially you
diffused the anger.

00:49:02.410 --> 00:49:04.494 align:middle line:84%
You diffused all of the anger
and resentment that goes--

00:49:04.494 --> 00:49:05.460 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Well, it came up a lot.

00:49:05.460 --> 00:49:06.510 align:middle line:84%
It just kept coming up.
-Yeah.

00:49:06.510 --> 00:49:07.930 align:middle line:84%
And then to catch
it and work with them

00:49:07.930 --> 00:49:10.750 align:middle line:84%
and help and-- each one of
them, and help them then

00:49:10.750 --> 00:49:12.520 align:middle line:90%
try to hear each other.

00:49:12.520 --> 00:49:14.810 align:middle line:84%
Would you say what you're
hearing another person say?

00:49:14.810 --> 00:49:17.605 align:middle line:84%
After they got enough
understanding for themselves.

00:49:17.605 --> 00:49:19.240 align:middle line:90%
And, yeah.

00:49:19.240 --> 00:49:22.670 align:middle line:84%
They got to the point at the
end-- it was very hard work.

00:49:22.670 --> 00:49:25.460 align:middle line:84%
It was many times that they
almost couldn't get through it.

00:49:25.460 --> 00:49:26.220 align:middle line:90%
But they did.

00:49:26.220 --> 00:49:32.110 align:middle line:84%
And we got to the end where they
were genuinely expressing care

00:49:32.110 --> 00:49:33.360 align:middle line:90%
and tenderness for each other.

00:49:33.360 --> 00:49:34.819 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Aw.
-And--

00:49:34.819 --> 00:49:36.597 align:middle line:84%
So you're saying if it
could happen with them--

00:49:36.597 --> 00:49:38.090 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: And they worked together.
-Yeah.

00:49:38.090 --> 00:49:39.910 align:middle line:84%
They found a solution
together to all the issues

00:49:39.910 --> 00:49:40.840 align:middle line:90%
that they had.

00:49:40.840 --> 00:49:42.420 align:middle line:84%
And they both felt
really good about it.

00:49:42.420 --> 00:49:45.170 align:middle line:84%
And after that, they were
able to work together

00:49:45.170 --> 00:49:46.890 align:middle line:90%
on various issues that came up.

00:49:46.890 --> 00:49:48.350 align:middle line:84%
They could talk to
each other again.

00:49:48.350 --> 00:49:49.630 align:middle line:90%
They could communicate.

00:49:49.630 --> 00:49:52.290 align:middle line:84%
And they had a pretty
good relationship.

00:49:52.290 --> 00:49:54.460 align:middle line:84%
Well, congratulations to
all three of you in that one

00:49:54.460 --> 00:49:56.080 align:middle line:84%
because they had to
be willing to show up.

00:49:56.080 --> 00:49:58.010 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, they were-- the
stakes were high enough.

00:49:58.010 --> 00:49:58.230 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Oh, they worked hard.

00:49:58.230 --> 00:49:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure there
are many people

00:49:59.550 --> 00:50:02.101 align:middle line:84%
listening to this who have
some high stakes going on too.

00:50:02.101 --> 00:50:02.800 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:50:02.800 --> 00:50:06.301 align:middle line:84%
That can feel the
beauty in this process.

00:50:06.301 --> 00:50:07.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean you--
JOHN: There is a way.

00:50:07.780 --> 00:50:12.840 align:middle line:84%
You would say-- would you say
that unless a person is really

00:50:12.840 --> 00:50:17.330 align:middle line:84%
mentally unstable to
the point that they

00:50:17.330 --> 00:50:19.720 align:middle line:84%
really-- like psychotic
behavior, for example.

00:50:19.720 --> 00:50:23.390 align:middle line:84%
Or this kind of
borderline personalities.

00:50:23.390 --> 00:50:26.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can't really work
with someone in that situation,

00:50:26.140 --> 00:50:27.320 align:middle line:90%
can you?

00:50:27.320 --> 00:50:32.960 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'd-- what you're
pointing to, the challenge is--

00:50:32.960 --> 00:50:33.660 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Yeah.

00:50:33.660 --> 00:50:35.089 align:middle line:84%
 --a lot higher.
REGINA: Yeah.

00:50:35.089 --> 00:50:37.420 align:middle line:84%
And what I like to be aware
of, though, if I have a label,

00:50:37.420 --> 00:50:39.380 align:middle line:84%
if I'm carrying a
label of somebody

00:50:39.380 --> 00:50:46.311 align:middle line:84%
of borderline or difficult
person or a narcissist or--

00:50:46.311 --> 00:50:47.200 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Right.
-Right.

00:50:47.200 --> 00:50:48.832 align:middle line:90%
Like that.

00:50:48.832 --> 00:50:50.770 align:middle line:84%
That what I've
learned over the years

00:50:50.770 --> 00:50:54.240 align:middle line:84%
is that that becomes-- if
that's who I see-- if I'm seeing

00:50:54.240 --> 00:50:57.300 align:middle line:84%
somebody through that
lens of that label--

00:50:57.300 --> 00:51:00.250 align:middle line:84%
and there's a difference
between being really

00:51:00.250 --> 00:51:03.350 align:middle line:84%
honest and clear about
what people's behaviors are

00:51:03.350 --> 00:51:04.670 align:middle line:84%
like I talked about earlier.
REGINA: Right.

00:51:04.670 --> 00:51:04.760 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:51:04.760 --> 00:51:06.960 align:middle line:84%
You can name the observation
of what I see you doing.

00:51:06.960 --> 00:51:09.240 align:middle line:84%
But it's a different step
to then take it into what's

00:51:09.240 --> 00:51:11.370 align:middle line:90%
the label to put on it.

00:51:11.370 --> 00:51:12.590 align:middle line:84%
And if you can keep
that seperate--

00:51:12.590 --> 00:51:13.656 align:middle line:90%
So if you've identified-- yeah.

00:51:13.656 --> 00:51:15.460 align:middle line:84%
If you've identified, OK,
I see what's going on here.

00:51:15.460 --> 00:51:16.540 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: I see the behavior.
-This is borderline person.

00:51:16.540 --> 00:51:17.880 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: And I can get
in touch with my--

00:51:17.880 --> 00:51:18.846 align:middle line:90%
They're a psychopath-- yeah.

00:51:18.846 --> 00:51:20.312 align:middle line:84%
-My unmet needs, right?
-Mmhmm.

00:51:20.312 --> 00:51:22.090 align:middle line:84%
So it's a difference
between saying what you are,

00:51:22.090 --> 00:51:27.020 align:middle line:84%
psychopath or borderline or
too-- I see these behaviors.

00:51:27.020 --> 00:51:31.630 align:middle line:84%
I feel scared,
worried, sad, or angry.

00:51:31.630 --> 00:51:32.360 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it might be.

00:51:32.360 --> 00:51:33.620 align:middle line:90%
But own my feelings.

00:51:33.620 --> 00:51:34.320 align:middle line:90%
They aren't about--

00:51:34.320 --> 00:51:35.430 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:51:35.430 --> 00:51:36.870 align:middle line:90%
Telling what's wrong with you.

00:51:36.870 --> 00:51:37.774 align:middle line:90%
But it's like, OK.

00:51:37.774 --> 00:51:39.240 align:middle line:84%
You're doing this and
I have these feelings.

00:51:39.240 --> 00:51:42.090 align:middle line:84%
And then what needs of mine
are not met by your behavior

00:51:42.090 --> 00:51:43.410 align:middle line:90%
that I could label in this way?

00:51:43.410 --> 00:51:44.590 align:middle line:84%
So have you found
these people--

00:51:44.590 --> 00:51:47.930 align:middle line:84%
even if you're taking a pretty
extreme kind of personality

00:51:47.930 --> 00:51:50.690 align:middle line:84%
disorder, it can also be
worked with in this way

00:51:50.690 --> 00:51:55.900 align:middle line:84%
even if there often isn't an
obvious sense of compassion

00:51:55.900 --> 00:51:56.920 align:middle line:90%
or empathy at all?

00:51:56.920 --> 00:51:59.714 align:middle line:84%
Maybe empathy appears to be
missing in their behaviors

00:51:59.714 --> 00:52:00.580 align:middle line:90%
throughout their lifetime?

00:52:00.580 --> 00:52:01.560 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yeah.
Right.

00:52:01.560 --> 00:52:03.560 align:middle line:84%
Can--and because I want to get
on to your kids in a minute.

00:52:03.560 --> 00:52:05.369 align:middle line:84%
From the mouths of babes.
-Yeah.

00:52:05.369 --> 00:52:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Just in short, can
people like this still

00:52:07.510 --> 00:52:09.591 align:middle line:84%
be worked with through
nonviolent communication

00:52:09.591 --> 00:52:10.290 align:middle line:90%
methods?

00:52:10.290 --> 00:52:12.720 align:middle line:84%
I like something that
I heard from Marshall

00:52:12.720 --> 00:52:13.890 align:middle line:90%
Rosenberg many years ago.

00:52:13.890 --> 00:52:16.840 align:middle line:84%
And it's just--it's
reverberated for me ever since.

00:52:16.840 --> 00:52:19.920 align:middle line:84%
Is that if we can
do-- if I can focus

00:52:19.920 --> 00:52:23.440 align:middle line:84%
my attention and my language
and this way of listening

00:52:23.440 --> 00:52:25.380 align:middle line:84%
and empathizing and
using these distinctions

00:52:25.380 --> 00:52:27.895 align:middle line:84%
I've been talking about,
then it's inevitable.

00:52:27.895 --> 00:52:28.680 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: OK.

00:52:28.680 --> 00:52:30.490 align:middle line:84%
That connection
and compassionate

00:52:30.490 --> 00:52:32.730 align:middle line:84%
giving and receiving is
another thing I learned.

00:52:32.730 --> 00:52:36.337 align:middle line:84%
That that way of being connected
as human beings is inevitable.

00:52:36.337 --> 00:52:37.670 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Regardless
of what's showing up.

00:52:37.670 --> 00:52:39.034 align:middle line:84%
If I stay with it.
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:52:39.034 --> 00:52:40.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's the thing that--
I think that's the hardest.

00:52:40.900 --> 00:52:42.490 align:middle line:90%
We give up because it's so hard.

00:52:42.490 --> 00:52:44.770 align:middle line:84%
And some-- being with
certain people, it's

00:52:44.770 --> 00:52:48.100 align:middle line:84%
just maybe more than we have
the skill or ability or capacity

00:52:48.100 --> 00:52:49.540 align:middle line:90%
or patience to deal with.

00:52:49.540 --> 00:52:53.250 align:middle line:84%
But I really-- I found that
over the years in my experience.

00:52:53.250 --> 00:52:58.320 align:middle line:84%
If I don't give in to
seeing you as this label

00:52:58.320 --> 00:53:00.700 align:middle line:84%
and I keep just seeing
you as doing these things,

00:53:00.700 --> 00:53:02.910 align:middle line:84%
not meeting the needs
for me, and what

00:53:02.910 --> 00:53:04.630 align:middle line:90%
needs could you be meeting.

00:53:04.630 --> 00:53:07.080 align:middle line:84%
So this idea I learned from
Marshall is so precious.

00:53:07.080 --> 00:53:09.660 align:middle line:84%
That everything people
do, if we can look at it,

00:53:09.660 --> 00:53:12.491 align:middle line:84%
is they're doing the best they
know how to meet their needs.

00:53:12.491 --> 00:53:13.190 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Absolutely.

00:53:13.190 --> 00:53:14.501 align:middle line:84%
If they knew a better
way, they would.

00:53:14.501 --> 00:53:15.200 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Beautiful.

00:53:15.200 --> 00:53:17.570 align:middle line:84%
And if I can see that,
I don't have to agree

00:53:17.570 --> 00:53:18.680 align:middle line:90%
or like their strategies.

00:53:18.680 --> 00:53:21.604 align:middle line:84%
I could be horrified by the way
they're meeting their needs.

00:53:21.604 --> 00:53:23.470 align:middle line:84%
But that is the best they
are capable of in the moment.

00:53:23.470 --> 00:53:24.830 align:middle line:84%
But if I can see
their needs behind it,

00:53:24.830 --> 00:53:27.661 align:middle line:84%
I feel a connection as a human
being to human being again.

00:53:27.661 --> 00:53:29.550 align:middle line:84%
-Yes.
-We're connected again.

00:53:29.550 --> 00:53:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And if I have that,
then there's hope--

00:53:31.310 --> 00:53:33.891 align:middle line:84%
there's always a possibility
for me that we can get to some--

00:53:33.891 --> 00:53:34.590 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:53:34.590 --> 00:53:35.723 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
really tough stuff.

00:53:35.723 --> 00:53:37.384 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about from
the mouths of babes

00:53:37.384 --> 00:53:38.890 align:middle line:84%
and your two little children.
JOHN: Yes.

00:53:38.890 --> 00:53:40.610 align:middle line:84%
Do you have a couple
little stories-- that you

00:53:40.610 --> 00:53:42.430 align:middle line:84%
just hinted at off camera.
REGINA: Yes.

00:53:42.430 --> 00:53:44.775 align:middle line:84%
I'd like hear about
your son, Argin.

00:53:44.775 --> 00:53:45.480 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: My son.

00:53:45.480 --> 00:53:47.240 align:middle line:84%
And your daughter, Terika.
JOHN: Yeah.

00:53:47.240 --> 00:53:48.520 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, so--

00:53:48.520 --> 00:53:49.865 align:middle line:90%
Because we-- little kids.

00:53:49.865 --> 00:53:50.970 align:middle line:84%
JOHN: Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:53:50.970 --> 00:53:51.880 align:middle line:90%
That's where it starts.

00:53:51.880 --> 00:53:52.920 align:middle line:90%
And parenting.

00:53:52.920 --> 00:53:56.520 align:middle line:84%
Parenting and having a family
has been one of my best

00:53:56.520 --> 00:53:57.920 align:middle line:90%
training grounds for--you know?

00:53:57.920 --> 00:53:59.150 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Absolutely.

00:53:59.150 --> 00:54:00.400 align:middle line:90%
Mediating conflict.

00:54:00.400 --> 00:54:02.680 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: So a couple
little short examples.

00:54:02.680 --> 00:54:04.080 align:middle line:90%
JOHN: Yeah.

00:54:04.080 --> 00:54:05.060 align:middle line:90%
So Argin.

00:54:05.060 --> 00:54:08.150 align:middle line:84%
There was a time a
while-- he's five now.

00:54:08.150 --> 00:54:09.690 align:middle line:90%
But it was a little while ago.

00:54:09.690 --> 00:54:13.630 align:middle line:84%
And he was--we were about
to have dinner and he

00:54:13.630 --> 00:54:14.760 align:middle line:90%
was sitting on the couch.

00:54:14.760 --> 00:54:16.110 align:middle line:90%
And we all got to the table.

00:54:16.110 --> 00:54:18.390 align:middle line:84%
And I said, Argin, come
over to dinner now.

00:54:18.390 --> 00:54:20.630 align:middle line:90%
We're going to have dinner.

00:54:20.630 --> 00:54:22.470 align:middle line:90%
Silence.

00:54:22.470 --> 00:54:24.330 align:middle line:84%
Argin, would you
come over to dinner?

00:54:24.330 --> 00:54:25.350 align:middle line:90%
And, nope.

00:54:25.350 --> 00:54:26.300 align:middle line:90%
Nope.

00:54:26.300 --> 00:54:27.396 align:middle line:90%
I'm playing.

00:54:27.396 --> 00:54:30.000 align:middle line:84%
He had this real kind
of tone to his voice.

00:54:30.000 --> 00:54:31.433 align:middle line:84%
Like, no.
You know?

00:54:31.433 --> 00:54:32.550 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:54:32.550 --> 00:54:35.675 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him a
few more times kind

00:54:35.675 --> 00:54:38.780 align:middle line:90%
of trying to be nice about it.

00:54:38.780 --> 00:54:40.730 align:middle line:84%
And then he just,
you know, he wouldn't

00:54:40.730 --> 00:54:44.370 align:middle line:84%
answer after-- so I got up
from the table to go over.

00:54:44.370 --> 00:54:46.220 align:middle line:90%
And I had this image in my mind.

00:54:46.220 --> 00:54:48.410 align:middle line:84%
I was going to take
the toy out of his hand

00:54:48.410 --> 00:54:50.490 align:middle line:84%
and bring him over to
the table, you know?

00:54:50.490 --> 00:54:51.730 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Mmhmm.
-And use some--

00:54:51.730 --> 00:54:52.540 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Be the enforcer.

00:54:52.540 --> 00:54:55.040 align:middle line:84%
 --gentle force to kind
of get him over there.

00:54:55.040 --> 00:54:57.321 align:middle line:84%
And, I mean, I notice
that I was triggered.

00:54:57.321 --> 00:54:58.020 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:54:58.020 --> 00:54:59.880 align:middle line:84%
I was having-- I
was kind of angry.

00:54:59.880 --> 00:55:01.450 align:middle line:84%
A little irritated.
You know?

00:55:01.450 --> 00:55:03.460 align:middle line:84%
And I had this image--
things going through my mind

00:55:03.460 --> 00:55:06.554 align:middle line:84%
about kind of disrespectful
and not caring about the family

00:55:06.554 --> 00:55:07.320 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:55:07.320 --> 00:55:08.870 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Respect again.
-Yeah.

00:55:08.870 --> 00:55:11.370 align:middle line:84%
And so I went over and--
but so I noticed it.

00:55:11.370 --> 00:55:13.190 align:middle line:84%
And as I got over to
the couch and I just

00:55:13.190 --> 00:55:15.950 align:middle line:84%
started to sit down next
to him, I caught myself

00:55:15.950 --> 00:55:17.020 align:middle line:90%
and I just took a breath.

00:55:17.020 --> 00:55:17.850 align:middle line:90%
I just took a breath.

00:55:17.850 --> 00:55:19.930 align:middle line:84%
And I have this-- I
have a lot of training

00:55:19.930 --> 00:55:23.490 align:middle line:84%
that I do with myself every
day that helps me to practice

00:55:23.490 --> 00:55:27.490 align:middle line:84%
that self-connection, connecting
into my breath, my body

00:55:27.490 --> 00:55:29.541 align:middle line:84%
sensations, and some
needs going on in me.

00:55:29.541 --> 00:55:30.240 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:55:30.240 --> 00:55:33.031 align:middle line:84%
So I just dropped
in there real quick.

00:55:33.031 --> 00:55:36.020 align:middle line:84%
Took a moment.
And then I looked up at him.

00:55:36.020 --> 00:55:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And I saw-- suddenly I just
saw something on his face

00:55:38.900 --> 00:55:40.890 align:middle line:90%
that he looked kind of angry.

00:55:40.890 --> 00:55:43.090 align:middle line:84%
But he also-- I
thought I saw something

00:55:43.090 --> 00:55:45.390 align:middle line:90%
that looked like sadness.

00:55:45.390 --> 00:55:47.940 align:middle line:84%
And so it was like this
fresh seeing of something.

00:55:47.940 --> 00:55:51.895 align:middle line:84%
And said, Argin-- and it
just came out of my mouth.

00:55:51.895 --> 00:55:54.510 align:middle line:84%
Argin, are you
angry but also sad?

00:55:54.510 --> 00:55:57.361 align:middle line:84%
Because-- and I had no idea
I was going to say this.

00:55:57.361 --> 00:55:58.060 align:middle line:90%
REGINA: Right.

00:55:58.060 --> 00:56:01.680 align:middle line:84%
It just came out in moment--
because I'm going on a trip

00:56:01.680 --> 00:56:02.440 align:middle line:90%
tomorrow?

00:56:02.440 --> 00:56:04.190 align:middle line:84%
REGINA: Aw.
OK.

00:56:04.190 --> 00:56:06.451 align:middle line:84%
And he just--
REGINA: Yeah.

00:56:06.451 --> 00:56:07.150 align:middle line:90%
 --stopped.

00:56:07.150 --> 00:56:10.625 align:middle line:84%
And he looked up at me
with these big brown eyes.

00:56:10.625 --> 00:56:11.860 align:middle line:90%
And he didn't say a word.

00:56:11.860 --> 00:56:13.659 align:middle line:84%
He just looked up at me.
REGINA: Yeah.

00:56:13.659 --> 00:56:14.981 align:middle line:84%
And I interpret
that as thank you.

00:56:14.981 --> 00:56:16.260 align:middle line:84%
-Yes.
-For hearing me.

00:56:16.260 --> 00:56:18.890 align:middle line:84%
And so you were able to
just stop yourself long

00:56:18.890 --> 00:56:20.670 align:middle line:90%
enough to touch in with him.

00:56:20.670 --> 00:56:22.540 align:middle line:84%
And this is what we all
need to do for each other.

00:56:22.540 --> 00:56:23.350 align:middle line:90%
And we're out of time.

00:56:23.350 --> 00:56:27.380 align:middle line:84%
But I want to say it seems to me
that nonviolent communication,

00:56:27.380 --> 00:56:31.990 align:middle line:84%
not just coming to you to
help mediate others' lives.

00:56:31.990 --> 00:56:33.770 align:middle line:84%
But we need-- this
is something that we

00:56:33.770 --> 00:56:35.920 align:middle line:84%
should actually be
able to take advantage

00:56:35.920 --> 00:56:37.360 align:middle line:90%
of and develop in ourselves.

00:56:37.360 --> 00:56:39.110 align:middle line:84%
And just really quickly,
we only have a couple

00:56:39.110 --> 00:56:41.040 align:middle line:90%
seconds left, is that possible?

00:56:41.040 --> 00:56:43.650 align:middle line:84%
Can people come in and
do personal training

00:56:43.650 --> 00:56:45.201 align:middle line:84%
for their own lives?
-Yes.

00:56:45.201 --> 00:56:46.020 align:middle line:84%
Definitely.
-Good.

00:56:46.020 --> 00:56:48.150 align:middle line:84%
We teach people how
they can mediate not only

00:56:48.150 --> 00:56:49.870 align:middle line:84%
for other people,
help other people,

00:56:49.870 --> 00:56:51.740 align:middle line:84%
but how you can mediate your
own conflicts with others

00:56:51.740 --> 00:56:53.970 align:middle line:84%
and your own inner
conflicts in a way

00:56:53.970 --> 00:56:55.610 align:middle line:84%
that-- with the same
principles of creating

00:56:55.610 --> 00:56:57.710 align:middle line:84%
that connection that leads
to this kind of compassion

00:56:57.710 --> 00:56:58.000 align:middle line:84%
that happens.
-Yes.

00:56:58.000 --> 00:56:59.260 align:middle line:84%
Very good.
Well, well done.

00:56:59.260 --> 00:57:00.880 align:middle line:84%
Fabulous work you
do in the world.

00:57:00.880 --> 00:57:03.930 align:middle line:84%
We need thousands if not
millions more of you.

